article.description: Victor Sanders scored 24 points to help Idaho slip past Santa Clara 69-59 in the Great Alaska Shootout on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Sanders helps Idaho slip past Santa Clara 69-59
article.linkText: Sanders helps Idaho slip past Santa Clara 69-59
article.story: ANCHORAGE, Alaska -- Victor Sanders scored 24 points to help Idaho slip past Santa Clara 69-59 in the Great Alaska Shootout on Wednesday night. The Vandals (3-1) led 25-24 at the break but fell behind early in the second half and trailed 50-40 midway. Sanders sank a 3-pointer to get them back on top, 60-59, with 3:08 to play, and then struck again from distance as part of a 9-0 finish for the final score. Perrion Callandret added 20 points, three rebounds and seven assists for the Vandals. Nate Sherwood chipped in nine points with five rebounds. Callandret's 5 of 5 from distance helped the team average 55 percent from 3-point range and 46 percent from the field overall. KJ Feagin led the Broncos (1-3) with 18 points and six assists. Santa Clara -- which averaged 38 percent shooting from the field -- has lost three straight after winning its opener against Division III La Verne.
